TITLE: Creating Basic Transactions in TinyBase
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to use transactions to wrap multiple store changes and reduce listener calls. It compares regular sequential mutations with a transaction that batches changes together.
SOURCE: https://github.com/tinyplex/tinybase/blob/main/site/guides/01_the_basics/6_transactions.md#2025-04-16_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import {createStore} from 'tinybase';

const store = createStore().setTables({pets: {fido: {species: 'dog'}}});
const listenerId = store.addRowListener('pets', 'fido', () =>
  console.log('Fido changed'),
);

// Multiple changes, not in a transaction
store.setCell('pets', 'fido', 'color', 'brown');
store.setCell('pets', 'fido', 'sold', false);
// -> 'Fido changed'
// -> 'Fido changed'

// Multiple changes in a transaction
store.transaction(() => {
  store.setCell('pets', 'fido', 'color', 'walnut');
  store.setCell('pets', 'fido', 'sold', true);
});
// -> 'Fido changed'

store.delListener(listenerId);
```

