TITLE: Creating Memoized Store with useCreateStore Hook in React
DESCRIPTION: Illustrates the use of useCreateStore hook to create a memoized TinyBase Store instance within a React component. This approach ensures that the Store is only created once, even if the component re-renders.
SOURCE: https://github.com/tinyplex/tinybase/blob/main/site/guides/02_building_uis/2_using_react_hooks.md#2025-04-16_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: jsx
CODE:
```
import {useCreateStore} from 'tinybase/ui-react';

const App4 = () => {
  const store = useCreateStore(() => {
    console.log('Store created');
    return createStore().setTables({pets: {fido: {species: 'dog'}}});
  });
  return <span>{store.getCell('pets', 'fido', 'species')}</span>;
};

root.render(<App4 />); // !act
// -> 'Store created'

root.render(<App4 />); // !act
// No second Store creation
```

