TITLE: Using useResultRowIds Hook with TinyBase Queries in React
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to use the useResultRowIds hook to reactively display query results in a React component. The example shows creating a store, defining a query, and using the hook to render the result.
SOURCE: https://github.com/tinyplex/tinybase/blob/main/site/guides/11_using_queries/3_building_a_ui_with_queries.md#2025-04-16_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: jsx
CODE:
```
import React from 'react';
import {createRoot} from 'react-dom/client';
import {createQueries, createStore} from 'tinybase';
import {useResultRowIds} from 'tinybase/ui-react';

