TITLE: Loading City Data into TinyBase Store
DESCRIPTION: Defines a function to load city data from a TSV file into a TinyBase store. It fetches the data, parses it, and uses a transaction to efficiently insert all records into the 'cities' table.
SOURCE: https://github.com/tinyplex/tinybase/blob/main/site/demos/06_city_database.md#2025-04-16_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const NUMERIC = /^[\d\.-]+$/;

const loadCities = async (store) => {
  const rows = (
    await (await fetch(`https://tinybase.org/assets/cities.tsv`)).text()
  ).split('\n');
  const cellIds = rows.shift().split('\t');
  store.transaction(() =>
    rows.forEach((row, rowId) =>
      row
        .split('\t')
        .forEach((cell, c) =>
          store.setCell(
            'cities',
            rowId,
            cellIds[c],
            NUMERIC.test(cell) ? parseFloat(cell) : cell,
          ),
        ),
    ),
  );
};

const CUSTOM_CELLS = [
  'Name',
  'Country',
  'Population',
  'Latitude',
  'Longitude',
  'Elevation',
];
```

