TITLE: Complex TinyQL Query Implementation
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates a complex query with joins, computed columns, grouping, and having clauses to analyze pet prices by state.
SOURCE: https://github.com/tinyplex/tinybase/blob/main/site/guides/11_using_queries/2_tinyql.md#2025-04-16_snippet_10

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
queries.setQueryDefinition(
  'query',
  'pets',
  ({select, join, where, group, having}) => {
    select('state', 'name').as('stateName');
    select(
      (getTableCell) =>
        getTableCell('species', 'price') * getTableCell('color', 'premium'),
    ).as('fullPrice');

    ['species', 'color', 'owner'].forEach((table) => join(table, `${table}Id`));
    join('region', 'owner', 'regionId').as('state');

    where('state', 'country', 'US');

    group('fullPrice', 'avg').as('avgFullPrice');

    having((getCell) => getCell('avgFullPrice') >= 5);
  },
);
```

