TITLE: Creating an Index of Word Stems for Fast Search
DESCRIPTION: Sets up a TinyBase index that registers each word in multiple slices based on its prefixes (stems) for efficient prefix-based search functionality.
SOURCE: https://github.com/tinyplex/tinybase/blob/main/site/demos/09_word_frequencies.md#2025-04-16_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const indexWords = (store) =>
  createIndexes(store).setIndexDefinition('stems', 'words', (getCell) => {
    const word = getCell('word');
    const stems = [];
    for (let l = 0; l <= word.length; l++) {
      stems.push(word.substring(0, l));
    }
    return stems;
  });
```

